elog_lib CHANGELOG
==================

- v1.0.5 | Apr 05 2026:

  [Fix] _elog_json_escape() now escapes all 32 C0 control characters (0x00-0x1F)
      per RFC 8259 §7; previously missed 27 including ESC (terminal injection vector)
  [Fix] All 6 file output handlers (file, audit, syslog_file, CEF, GELF, ELK) now
      refuse to write through symlinks via _elog_safe_append() guard
  [Fix] _elog_truncate_check() refuses to truncate symlinked log files, preventing
      TOCTOU symlink-following overwrite during log rotation
  [Fix] Signal trap save/restore in truncation prevents clobbering consumer handlers
  [Fix] Classic format output sanitizes embedded newlines to prevent log injection
  [Fix] elog_init() enforces chmod 640 on pre-existing log files, not only new files
  [New] ELOG_AUDIT_MAX_LINES: optional audit log size limit (default: 0 = disabled)
  [Change] Truncation refactored to parameterized _elog_truncate_check_file() shared
      by app log and audit log; bare cat changed to command cat
  [Change] CI: batsman 1.4.0 → 1.4.1; CI workflow pin v1.0.3 → v1.4.1

- v1.0.4 | Mar 23 2026:

  [Change] README restructured to floor-level documentation convention: numbered
      sections, flat-square badges, centered badge row, bold one-liner, copyright
      blockquote, exit codes table, ## 3. Configuration and ## 4. Usage sections

- v1.0.4 | Mar 16 2026:

  [Fix] JSON-escape _host, _app, _level in elog() and elog_event() JSON output;
      matches defensive pattern already used by GELF and ELK formatters
  [Fix] _elog_json_escape() now handles \b (backspace) and \f (form feed) per RFC 8259
  [Fix] CEF extension key names sanitized to prevent structure corruption
  [Fix] Bare rm in _elog_truncate_check() changed to command rm per alias-safety convention
  [Fix] elog_init() sets umask 027 during file/directory creation, restores on all paths
  [Fix] Temp file cleanup trap in _elog_truncate_check() for signal safety
  [Fix] Legacy symlink creation simplified to avoid TOCTOU race
  [Fix] Version header comment synced with ELOG_LIB_VERSION
  [Change] Internal helpers converted from echo-return to result-variable pattern,
      eliminating ~70% of per-call subshell fork overhead
  [Change] Hostname cached at first use; eliminates repeated fork+exec across 3 call sites
  [Change] Timestamps computed from single date invocation (was 2 per call)
  [Change] SIEM module gating uses O(1) cached index lookup (was O(n) linear scan)
  [Change] Shared _elog_parse_extras() replaces 3x copy-paste parsing loop
  [Change] Unreachable 42-line direct-write fallback removed from elog()

- v1.0.3 | Mar 11 2026:

  [Fix] host field in all JSON output (elog_log, elog_event, syslog UDP) now
      uses FQDN via hostname -f with fallback to short name, then bare hostname;
      aligns with RFC 5424 HOSTNAME field recommendation and improves host
      disambiguation in multi-domain log aggregation environments

- v1.0.2 | Mar 07 2026:

  [Fix] ELOG_AUDIT_FILE expansion in elog_init() changed from ${:-} to ${-}
      so consumers can set ELOG_AUDIT_FILE="" to disable audit logging
  [Fix] elog_logrotate_snippet() respects empty ELOG_AUDIT_FILE (omits from
      rotation config when audit is disabled)
  [New] README: integration guide, configuration profiles, use cases, and
      troubleshooting sections

- v1.0.1 | Mar 07 2026:
  [New] CEF output module with ArcSight Common Event Format (v0) support
  [New] CEF severity mapping (debug=1, info=3, warn=5, error=7, critical=10)
  [New] CEF header and extension escaping (pipe, backslash, equals, newline)
  [New] Syslog UDP output module with RFC 5424 and RFC 3164 format support
  [New] Fire-and-forget UDP delivery via /dev/udp with nc fallback
  [New] Syslog severity mapping and PRI calculation (facility * 8 + severity)
  [New] Configurable syslog payload format (classic, json, cef)
  [New] Event context staging for SIEM handler access to structured event data
  [New] GELF output module with Graylog Extended Log Format 1.1 support
  [New] GELF timestamp conversion to Unix epoch via _elog_ts_epoch()
  [New] GELF short_message truncation at 256 chars with full_message for overflow
  [New] GELF transport selection: UDP (reusing _elog_udp_send) or HTTP
  [New] GELF custom fields with underscore prefix (_app, _pid, _event_type, _tag)
  [New] ELK JSON output module with ECS (Elastic Common Schema) field alignment
  [New] ECS category mapping from elog taxonomy (intrusion_detection, configuration,
      network, notification, process)
  [New] ECS event.type mapping (denied, allowed, change, start, end, error, info)
  [New] HTTP delivery infrastructure with curl/wget auto-detection and fallback
  [New] Fire-and-forget HTTP POST via background subshell (_elog_http_send)
  [New] 57 new tests across CEF, syslog UDP, GELF, and ELK test suites
  [Fix] Trailing newline from here-string stripped in CEF, GELF, and ELK extras parsing
  [Fix] UDP detection probe in elog_init() gated by elog_output_enabled
      instead of _elog_output_find (probe only fires when module is enabled)
  [Fix] CEF signatureId field header-escaped for defensive correctness

- v1.0.0 | Mar 06 2026:
  [New] Standalone elog_lib repository extracted from BFD elog_lib.sh v1.0.0
  [New] Deterministic log file architecture: dual log model (application + audit)
  [New] elog_init() for log environment setup (directory, permissions, symlinks)
  [New] elog_logrotate_snippet() generator for logrotate config
  [New] Output module registry with parallel indexed arrays (file, audit_file, syslog_file, stdout)
  [New] Source filtering per output module (all, elog, event)
  [New] Log truncation support via ELOG_LOG_MAX_LINES (inode-safe)
  [New] Legacy symlink support via ELOG_LEGACY_LOG
  [New] Backward-compatible elog() API with dispatch-based routing
  [New] BATS test suite with batsman CI (9-OS matrix)
  [New] elog_event() structured event envelope with JSON dispatch to audit log
  [New] Event taxonomy with 23 canonical types across 7 categories
  [New] Default severity mapping via _elog_event_severity() (error/warn/info)
  [New] elog_critical() convenience wrapper completing 5-level API symmetry
  [New] Backward compatibility test suite validating no-init drop-in pattern
  [New] README.md with full API reference, event taxonomy, and usage guide
  [Change] Extract _elog_auto_enable() helper from elog() for DRY pre-init fallback
